section.def:
classroom
                                                (課室) means any
                                    room used for teaching purposes;

dormitory
                                                (集體寢室) means any
                                    room provided as sleeping accommodation for boarders;

paragraph.content:
a floor space at least 1.5 m in width for the use of the teacher, extending
                    along the whole length of the wall in front of the pupils;
                    and

a floor space at least 1.5 m in width for the use of the teacher, extending
                    along the whole length of the wall in front of the pupils in the
                    classroom;

subsection.def:
profits
                    (利潤) means any profits or net income arising
                from a business or trading undertaking, or a business or trading arrangement,
                referred to in paragraph (1);

paragraph.content:
the other members of the management committee concerned contravened
                        regulation 99A(1) or (3) without his knowledge or consent;
                    or

paragraph.continued:
one
                    pan and 2 urinals for every 30
                    pupils;

one
                    pan and one urinal for every 15
                    boarders;

subparagraph.content:
The Hong Kong Polytechnic University established by The Hong Kong
                        Polytechnic University Ordinance (Cap.
                        1075);

The Chinese University of Hong Kong established by The Chinese
                        University of Hong Kong Ordinance (Cap.
                        1109);

The Hong Kong Academy for Performing Arts established by The Hong Kong
                        Academy for Performing Arts Ordinance (Cap.
                            1135);

paragraph.content:
Grade E or higher grade in English Language (Syllabus B) in the Hong Kong
                    Certificate of Education
                    Examination;

a pass in English Language in the Hong Kong English School Certificate, the
                    Hong Kong Chinese School Certificate, or the Hong Kong School Certificate;
                    or

A certificate of status as “Qualified Assistant Kindergarten Teacher”
                    issued by the Hong Kong Education Department to a teacher who has completed an
                    approved course of training, and approved teaching experience;
